{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17596297","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17596297"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:11:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:11:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15401"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15401","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15401"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.64,0,0.04,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8092"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63366"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8092","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8092"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15401"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48817"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8108"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19632"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19636"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20724"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63366","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63366"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDiverticulitis is characterised by inflammation of colonic diverticula (Image) that can lead to various complications. One such complication is fistula formation. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of fistula formation in diverticulitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Bacterial invasion creates tunnels between organs","Chronic inflammation leads to tissue erosion between adjacent structures","Lymphatic obstruction causes channel formation","Congenital weakness in tissue planes allows communication","Direct mechanical perforation creates immediate connections"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn diverticulitis, \u003Cstrong\u003Echronic inflammation\u003C/strong\u003E of the colonic wall leads to tissue damage and the formation of abscesses. These inflammatory processes can gradually erode through tissue planes, creating abnormal connections (fistulas) between the colon and adjacent structures. One such abnormal connection is between the colon and the urinary bladder - a colovesical fistula. Colovaginal and colocutaneous fistulas are much less frequently encountered.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect mechanical perforation\u003C/strong\u003E would cause acute peritonitis rather than fistula formation. \u003Cstrong\u003EBacterial invasion\u003C/strong\u003E alone does not create fistulous tracts without the inflammatory process. There is no evidence that \u003Cstrong\u003Econgenital weakness\u003C/strong\u003E predisposes to fistula formation in diverticulitis. \u003Cstrong\u003ELymphatic obstruction\u003C/strong\u003E is not a mechanism for fistula formation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A fistula is an abnormal connection between two epithelial surfaces.","Diverticulitis can lead to fistula formation through inflammation and abscess formation that erodes into adjacent structures.","Colovesical fistulas are the most common type of fistula associated with diverticulitis."],"references":["Piscopo N, Ellul P. Diverticular Disease: A Review on Pathophysiology and Recent Evidence. Ulster Med J. 2020 Sep;89(2):83-88. Epub 2020 Oct 21. PMID: 33093692; PMCID: PMC7576390","Feuerstein JD, Falchuk KR. Diverticulosis and Diverticulitis. Mayo Clin Proc. 2016 Aug;91(8):1094-104. doi: 10.1016/j.mayocp.2016.03.012. Epub 2016 May 5. PMID: 27156370","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48817"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15401"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21203"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21203","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21203"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/72JBK9xgiKvgHveyzbLZzGhqeo4qTy.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/72JBK9xgiKvgHveyzbLZzGhqeo4qTy.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":514,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48817","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48817"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-20T20:34:19+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-20T20:35:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8092"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63366"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"h